inn1.comm: fullish ball, almost a yorker, but wide enough to drive to point
fullish again and he pushes that across to the on-side
there's runs now as he takes a full ball from about off stump and turns it past Benn at midwicket, whi runs after it and cuts it down near the boundary
yorker-length delivery and Watson just pushes it back to Taylor
some outswing for Taylor now as he lands that one of a full length and Watson leaves it be

and now there's a wicket, a big one too, to cap what could be the longest first over ever! Taylor pitches very full and angles the ball in through the air, Watson expects it to move away and doesn't get his front foot out too much but the ball dips and clips him flush on the foot
good length outside off, swings in very close as Marsh opts to leave
now he pitches it wider and moves it away from Marsh, who cannot stop having a flirt and very nearly edges it to Browne, the wicketkeeper
movement again, and some bounce, as Marsh allows that one pass
pitches on leg and straightens and Marsh pushes it back past Ponting, calling for the run as he takes on to the danger end, mid-off running in fast
and he leaves first ball, planting his front foot well in and raising arms
fuller ball, much fuller, and he drives it to cover, who is sharp to stop it
full with movement through the air, pitches on off and turned to midwicket by Marsh, getting the bat down in time
not as full and a bit wider, still swinging though, and Marsh leaves
close one, as Marsh pushes at another swinging fuller delivery and gets an inside-edge onto front pad before Ponting calls for the single to square leg
good ball, pitching on middle and off and straightening and Ponting, inching across his stumps, has to defend that back to Taylor
but thats too straight and in Ponting's area, so he gets off the mark with a pleasing clip off the pads and the fast outfield does the rest
good comeback delivery, on a length and he gets forward to defend
angled across Marsh, with swing and lift, and he shoulders arms
short of a length, again with lovely carry to Browne, and Marsh leaves
very full outside off stump and he squeezes it past gully for a couple
top delivery! Thats a good length, with seam and lift, to beat Marsh as he pushes forward and misses by a whisker, Browne takes it up at a good height too
back of a length and seaming away and Marsh allows this to go by
tries to get the yorker right and Marsh punches straight to cover
some movement through the air but fraction too full and Ponting pushes that off the front foot and picks the gap wide of Benn at extra cover, running hard
dragged in short and he's hurried into the shot, but plays it well and makes sure to keep it along the ground, tucking the ball into the gap at square leg
full now and he drives it across towards mid-on, who runs in
back of a length and wide, but it swings back in so Marsh leaves it be
moves away this time but its wide enough for Marsh to leave again
swings in and he clips that from off stump, in the air wide of midwicket
edged and taken! Powell bowls it short of a length and Marsh, trying to steer it down to third man, doesn't get over the bounce and tickles it to Browne, silly shot that
short of a length and he defends it to backward point, calling for one as Ponting hesitates but they end up running through for the single
lands it on a good length, Ponting strides in and shoulders arms
good length outside off and he leaves it be this time as well
full and wide, Ponting drives but mistimes it, scooping it over Bravo's fingers at backward point and thats his second boundary of the morning, albeit streakily
better length and he drives it back to Powell, who feigns a throw back
good length on middle and off and Clarke patiently defends it back
back of a length, slightly wider, and he opts to leave that alone
shorter one outside off, he gets up and pushes it backward point
short again and he gets onto the toes, punching to cover this time
tidy line from Taylor gets Clarke defending again, telling Ponting to wait
invites the drive but he gets forward and leaves, ending a maiden over

yowza! That one's full and swinging in exaggeratedly off the pitch, producing a loose drive from Ponting and the ball nips back between bat and pad and Browne has to fling himself around to stop the ball from carrying on further
too full and on the pads and he clips it down to fine leg for one
good length again, pitching and straightening, and Clarke leaves
gets a massive stride in and defends that one to the man at cover
top shot, Clarke just planting his front foot forward and putting the half-volley away past extra cover
two in two, this one punched straight back past the stumps and some sloppy fielding on the boundary down there gives away the four
change of pace, landing on a full length and straightening away to beat Ponting's bat as he defends off the front foot
this time he gets more forward and defends a good ball to cover
full this time as he looks for swing but wide enough for Ponting to leave
short on the stumps and Ponting hooks in the air but it drops before the man down near the ropes at fine leg
lands on a length wide of off stump and Clarke pushes away from his body, playing it wide of the lone slip and backward point for a single
caught! Slower ball works as Ponting shuffles across and clips this in the air, indifferently, lazily, straight to Gayle at short midwicket, who falls to his right and clutches on
comes back in sharply, Clarke gets tall and lets the ball sails over the stumps
good ball, short of a length and Clarke shoulders arms to it that time
a touch fuller and straighter and he drives to mid-off, who slides and saves it
short of a length and he gets up again, defending it down to point
slower ball, fuller length and that one's clipped to short midwicket
good length ball draws a defensive shot to cover, ending a maiden over
gets him shouldering arms first ball with one short of a good length
full this time, moving through the air and he punches it to cover-point
lands on middle and straightens and Hussey taps it back to Taylor
now he draws him forward with one outside off, stopped by Bravo
slower ball, wider and inviting the drive but Hussey, nearly playing, leaves
second maiden in a row, Hussey leaving a wide one be off the front foot
back of a length and he shoulder arms as the ball starts to lift
pitches in line and comes in, Clarke shuffles and drives to midwicket
bowls a tempting fullish one outside off and Clarke shoulders arms
nips back in very sharply and pings him on the inside of the thigh, that will leave a bruise or red spot for a while
straighter one and Clarke gets forward to defend it back
this one comes in and Clarke turns it to the fielder at midwicket
works it across Hussey, back of a length, and he watches it go past
short of a length and he defends with an inside-edge onto his boot
straighter one, change of pace, and defended back to Bravo
thats full and angled across Hussey, who leaves it be for Browne
even fuller and Hussey defends solidly off the front foot to cover
pushes at one seaming across off a shorter length and gets beaten
straighter one on the stumps, Clarke falls across and drives to mid-on
now there's a single, with Clarke getting on top of the bounce and pushing into the covers, where a sliding stop can't cut off the quick run
short one, lifting off the track as it angles across Hussey, who watches it
follows up with a fuller one, firmly driven off the front foot to cover
hustles his first run to get off the mark after 15 deliveries, cramped by a short one that cuts back in but he gets bat on it and drops the ball near the slips, Clarke calls him down for the single
another one short of a length, jagging back in, is loosely played to point off the thigh as Clarke falls over and misses out on the shot, Powell has a smile and a word of advice
full and going away, he chases it with a drive and inside-edges onto pad
gets forward and leaves that one, Bravo bowling a top-class line here
leaves off the front foot again, the ball swinging away from off stump
its like a Test match, Hussey patiently defending a good ball to cover
uses his feet this time but can only defend the ball as Bravo spots him coming and alters the length, top stuff this
ends a good over with one back of a length and its defended well
gets onto the back foot and punches the ball to an ambidextrous Marshall in the covers, who dives to one side and releases with the other hand
super ball, nipping back in through the gap between bat and body, nearly cutting Clarke in half and there's noise but its ball brushing thigh through to Browne
too straight on this occasion and he's sharp to on-drive a quick single
short of a length and Hussey steers this one to backward point
good ball, lands outside leg and seams across and Hussey defends
good ball again, this time Hussey defends getting back
swings in off a length and Clarke defends to Marshall at short cover
shorter and he quickly gets back, punching to short cover again
gets back and drops this one to backward point, Hussey initiates the manic single from the other end, Clarke sets off and the fielder misses the stumps
now he plays a shot, getting over one angled across and steering into the gap between the slips and backward point for a single
uses his feet and drives handsomely but can't beat a moving mid-off
gets back in his crease and tries to softly steal another single towards backward point but Chanderpaul swoops in rapidly to cut off any such thoughts
starts off with a short one, which Hussey tucks to midwicket
short again and Hussey places a poor pull shot, ball taking the splice of the bat very high and nearly lobbing to mid-on, but he's slow to react and the ball lands safe
no pace but a tidier line, back of a length, and Clarke shuffles to defend
comes well down the track and defends a shorter one from Sammy
sees some room but can only get up and chop the ball to point
steals a single last ball, using his feet and pushing back past the stumps
fuller ball outside off, swings in, Clarke pushes to short cover
swings through the air and lands full, Clarke gets in and on-drives
gets onto the front foot and drives again, failing to beat short cover
moves forward and punches the ball to cover, who also stops it
thats too wide and he cuts over the ball, getting a single out to Powell running across from third man, who returns a good throw to keep them to one
worked across him at a good height and he watches it go to Browne
gets onto the front foot and plays a pleasing drive, but right to cover
single now, but courtesy an inside-edge to square leg as he defends
change of pace, good length on off stump and he plods it back
good shot, getting over the bounce and guiding a single to third man
too straight and he turns that into the gap at square leg
fullish ball outside off stump and he drives well to extra cover
short of a length, no room to work with, and he defends off the back foot
plays and misses at one that kicks up and he admonishes himself
now he comes down the pitch, smothering the ball to cover
advances down and drives into the gap at cover, single out to sweeper
walks way across his stumps to the off side, Bravo sees him and drags it in short, and umpire Asad Rauf spreads his arms
another wide, this one sliding down leg stump, raises 50 in the 21st over
shuffles across and on-drives, but Bravo reacts and saves a single
nearly pops a return catch back to Bravo as this one stops on him, Clarke plays with one hand off the bat but the ball drops to the right of Bravo
there's a single as the ball strays and Hussey nudges to square leg
gentle stuff, no real movement, and he defends off the front foot
gets forward, well outside his crease, and drives a slow ball to mid-off
shuffles around and nudges a straighter one down to fine leg
this one seams across and beats bat as he pokes at it away from his body, the most gentle bit of movement off the scrambled seam does the trick that time .. well, almost
bit too full and Hussey comes forward to drive towards extra cover
pushed across the stumps and he leaves it be
fuller and wider and he again leaves it be for Browne
short and he pulls past midwicket, wanting two immediately
picks up one more, dabbing a wide one past backward point
good length on middle and off, straightens, Clarke drives it back
eases onto the front foot, pushes a single to a sluggish Gayle at cover
gets back and across and on-drives off the toes to Marshall at mid-on
gets up and steers a short one past backward point for one more
a bit too wide and now its Clarke's turn to dab the ball to third man
good length ball on off stump, Hussey drops his head and defends
gets forward and blocks this one out as well, in no hurry at all
tidy stuff again, landing on middle and leg and watchfully patted back
bounced in short and he misses out on the pull, pirouetting, plays too early
fuller and straighter, bunted back but Bravo dives across to field
well played, working the shorter one across the line, but to the fielder
swings in and he clips it nicely past midwicket to Taylor
short, wide and crunched away off the back foot to deep point
fuller and straighter and he drives it towards mid-on to keep strike
short and it sits up and he plays an uppercut, getting airborne, but the tennis-ball bounce defeats him
a boundary .. bring out the drums! Clarke sashays down and thumps this one over Sammy to long-off ... thats been about 101 balls since the last four
short and wide and he gets across, cutting into the covers
full on middle and off and he pushes the ball to cover
no room to work with but he pushes this one to point, well done
defends the last ball back to Sammy patiently
good start, he pitches it on line and it moves away off the pitch, beating Hussey's edge
outside off again, this time Hussey waits and guides it through the vacant slip region for a single
a bit of bounce for Pollard, but at his pace Clarke has no problem pushing it away to off for a single
defended away to cover
Hussey waits again and helps it on its way down to third man
and now Clarke does the same thing, outside off and he angles the bat to guide it fine for an easy single
he's around the wicket with one slip, Clarke cuts to point
bit of turn now, past the outside edge, good bowling
Clarke pushes this one away to cover
Clarke forward now, smothers any spin and pushes back to the bowler
no real turn on this one, Benn tosses it up outside off and Clarke defends

and there's a big chance that's gone begging! Benn did get this one to turn, pitching outside off and spinning further away, Clarke tries to cut but gets an edge to first slip. Bravo has moved to his right and the ball went to his left, he didn't even get a hand on it, but really that should have been a comfortable catch, he just moved the wrong way
defended away to point
good shot, Hussey's first boundary as he seizes on a short one from the medium-pacer and pulls confidently forward of midwicket.
driven away to deep cover and there's an easy run
pushed away defensively
on off stump, good line and Clarke nudges it away forward of point
cut fine, there's more easy singles to third man
spins in to the stumps, Hussey defends
Hussey pushes away to cover and there's no run
this one spins and bounces too much, it's darted down leg side and Browne can't glove it, the ball runs away to the boundary
Hussey leaves outside off
turns in towards off, Hussey tucks it away square
Benn curves this one in towards the stumps, Clarke uses his feet and drives down to long on
just a little spin, Hussey turns it to square leg and they scamper through for a tight single
darted in, Hussey pushes a quick single towards point
tossed up a fraction, Clarke tries a big swat and edgily gets it away behind square, not where he intended
flatter and wider outside off, Clarke cuts but there's a short third man who stops any run
turns in to Clarke, who defends
on the stumps, Clarke gets down for a paddle sweep that is collected at fine leg
angled in to Hussey, who defends
straight ball, Clarke defends
pushed away to deep cover and there's an easy single
pitches around off stump and turns down leg, Hussey tries to glance and doesn't connect, then wonders why it wasn't called a wide, which is a good question
nudged away to point for a quick run
prods this one away to cover
and Clarke attacks now, Benn pitches wide of off, Clarke gets forward and sweeps along the ground through midwicket, a good safe shot that gets the scoreboard ticking over
Hussey tries to reverse sweep, doesn't connect and the ball strikes him on the pad, it was heading down leg though
pushed away to leg
defends on the front foot
this time Hussey's reverse sweep does work, he gets it fine for a couple
pushed away for a quick single into the off side

very good shot from Clarke, Gayle pushing them through a tad quickly and Clarke waits, then with very soft hands cuts it so fine that it would have gone between the keeper and first slip, not that there was a slip, and it runs away for four. Excellent thinking from Clarke
turns toward Hussey's pads now, he works it away through square leg
Clarke rocks back now and cuts square, Benn just a fraction too short that time
quite a bit of turn in towards Hussey, he tries to tuck it away fine but can't get a run
pushed out forward of point this time
on the pads, Clarke nudges an easy single to long on and that's his half-century
pushed away into the off side, easy runs for Australia here and West Indies just can't build up the pressure
nudged away towards cover
there's some turn, Hussey tries to sweep and can't connect
spins it away from Hussey again, but no real drift from Gayle and Hussey works a run forward of point
cut away to point and there's an easy single where there probably shouldn't have been one
guided away forward of point, they push through for two and West Indies are not switched on in the field here, that should have been kept to one
down leg side, Hussey can't get bat on ball and Asad Rauf, after a long while to make his decision, calls it wide
another reverse sweep doesn't come off for Hussey, hit on the pads but Gayle's angle is taking it down leg side
Clarke uses his feet and gets to the pitch of the ball, clipping a run to long on
Hussey sweeps, beats Chanderpaul at square leg and gets a single into the deep
pushed to cover
an appeal for lbw, Clarke tried to sweep but couldn't connect, the ball clearly spinning past off stump
another easy single, Clarke just finding the gaps so comfortably here
tossed up outside off, Hussey drives hard but straight to cover
tip and run from Clarke, he nudges to cover and takes off immediately, Bravo's throw to the bowler's end missed but Clarke was home in any case
slower ball, Hussey forward and driving through cover, Hussey pushes for two and puts the pressure on the man in the deep, a fumble lets them get back
pushed to midwicket for an easy run
Clarke prods defensively back down the pitch
angled in to the pads, Clarke clips it forward of square and despite another fumble in the deep from Bravo this time, they only get a single
short ball, not a bad one from Powell, Hussey shapes to hook and then lets it go
dropped! Clarke drives it back to Benn's left, he hurls the hand out in hope and it bounces out, really tough chance, those either stick or they don't.
cut away for a single
Hussey sweeps, can't beat the man behind square

tossed up outside off, Hussey picks this one up early and sweeps with the turn, it flies over deep midwicket and bounces just over the rope, Pollard dives in the deep but he was never really near that one. First six of the innings
flatter this time from Benn, Hussey tucks a single square

and Benn breaks through! He's coming around the wicket, sends in a quicker ball that pitches on off, Clarke is walking across and trying to clip through leg, he's struck in line and that was not spinning, probably taking leg stump

and he's nearly taken, but dropped by Bravo! Hussey pokes feebly at shortish one and the ball balloons up off the shoulder towards backward point but Bravo, diving forward, cannot hold on with his left hand .. he should have attempted it with two hands, so a chance goes down
back of a length and he shoulders arms
and again, ball comes back in and he leaves it be
off the mark now, shuffling and tickling it to fine leg for one
comes forward and pushes into the covers
comes in with the angle and he opens the face, steering to third man
comes well forward and defends
gets back and cuts but cannot beat the fielders
too straight and he gets down, paddling into the gap for a couple
flat on middle and off, defended back towards Benn
gets back and cuts but cannot beat the man at backward point
cuts hard and the ball nearly flies to short third man
loosener, overpitched and he drives past cover, calling for two
straighter one, gets across and drives but mid-on comes around
full and he reaches out, mistiming the drive into the covers
streaky shot to bring up a hard-earned fifty, Hussey chasing one and edging smack past where a slip could have been, third man cannot get across and he gets a four
edged but this one doesn't carry to the wicketkeeper, Taylor slipping in the slower, split-fingered ball which Hussey nibbles at, the ball drops a couple feet before Browne
times this one better, guiding it into the gap at gully for one
flat on middle and leg, Hussey walks across and turns it away
flat and a tad full, White gets across and paddles past square leg
pushed in quicker, forcing Hussey to wait and dab it to short third man
again he gets back and pokes at it, this time with an inside-edge
waits to see if it spins, and it doesn't, so he plays it to midwicket
some turn there, spinning back in and White cuts past the 'keeper
dances down, mistiming the drive over mid-off and it drops safely in front of the fielder running in ... Hussey wants to get on with it now that he's got fifty
well bowled, as he sees White advancing, holds back the length and White can only turn it to midwicket
well played, working the wrists to turn the slower and straighter ball past the man positioned at short fine leg, getting White a couple more
full on off stump, he plods forward and pats it back to the bowler
shorter in length and he's hurried into a back-foot punch to point
changes of pace and White's onto the front foot and driving way too early, somehow the ball sneaks back as he withdraws a hand off the bat, but Browne sloppily fumbles and allows two byes
full and flat on the stumps, up goes the back leg as he clips to midwicket
there's a big shot, as White sizes up midwicket, but fails to connect
comes forward, waits, and crunches a wide one powerfully past cover
quicker and flatter, on middle and off, and driven to midwicket
dances down, exposing his stumps, Benn follows him but Hussey drives in the air down to long-on
gets across and paddles from outside off down to fine leg for two
full on the stumps, he uses his feet and drives into the gap for one
poor ball, wrong line, low a full toss gift-wrapped on White's pads and he easily clips that down into the gap, beating the man running around from fine leg
slower ball, but short and wide, he has to really wait on it and then gives it a hard thump out to the man at deep point sweeper
another low full toss as Bravo strives for a yorker but struggles, White comes out and hammers it out to deep cover this time
full outside leg stump and clipped out to Chanderpaul at deep midwicket
full on leg stump and a tiring Hussey can only chip that in the air down to long-on, where Marshall settles under an easy catch, ending a patient and crucial 62
plays and edges first ball, playing against the turn and edging past Browne down towards third man
just too short and Hopes places that superbly past point and gully, sweeper is also too far in front so that races away to the boundary ropes
better stuff, turning and bouncing and beating his back-foot prod
looped up and dipping outside off, he gets struck outside the line of impact
flatter this time and Hopes drives it back to Benn
some more room but he can only thump that off the front foot to point
well bowled, a spot-on yorker on middle and off, slower too, has White jamming the bat down just in time and Bravo fields himself
not quite right this time and White clips off the pads to midwicket
well done again, yorker on off stump, he jams bat down and the ball sneaks through this legs for a scampered single towards square leg
very full outside off stump and thats driven out to deep cover sweeper
full on off stump and turned away off the front pad to deep midwicket
nearly a yorker but not quite, yet its only a driven single to mid-on
poor stuff, a front-foot no-ball, and he gives White room to cut past point
gives him more room, White cuts up and over point, not timed well and Pollard does well to run across in front of square and keep them to two
powerful shot, White makes room and muscles this very straight and a sliding long-on cannot get there, that shot came up because of the length Taylor bowled

good grief, Fletcher's dropped him at deep square leg! White went hooking a short ball, undone by the sluggish bounce, but Taylor is let down by his fielder, keeping his eyes on it but not settling himself and spilling a simple catch, in and out
short again and this one's worked along the ground to Fletcher
onto the front foot, slashing through the covers for one
short on the stumps and he pulls over the man at midwicket, the slowness of the track not allowing the ball to come on, and the sweeper runs in to field
makes room and skips down, Bravo knew he was coming and bowled it short and wide and Hopes swats it off the toe end of the bat down to mid-off
full and down leg stump as he sees White moving about, well bowled, so thats a clipped couple more to the score out to deep fine leg
slower ball, White swings with his eyes shut, fails to connect, and another silly fumble by Browne gives up a run ... he's had a poor day behind the stumps
oh well done Bravo, following Hopes and honing a yorker into the pads, causing him to fall over onto his knees as the ball takes him out, excellent bowling
doesn't get it right this time and Hopes flicks two to deep fine leg
well done, nearly a yorker on leg stump, clipped in the air over midwicket
in the blockhole, nearly, and White swings it down to long-on

drops in a bouncer with no pace on it at all, Hopes swats and misses and the umpire calls it wide as it misses his bat ... Taylor doesn't like the call, marginally above the head, but not enough to be called wide
swings hard again, doesn't get it out of the screws, but one to midwicket
full and right up there, White heaves it along the ground to midwicket
slips out a loopy full toss which Hopes can't put away, flicked to the deep
another drop! White backs away and slices a slower ball to Gayle at extra cover, who leaps up full stretch and gets fingers to it, failing to latch on
bouncer to end the over, Hopes backs away and flays at it, trying to uppercut it over gully but the ball beats him so Australia are kept to 213 for 5

inn2.comm: and there's a wicket first ball! Marshall gets a regulation edge behind off Lee and Ronchi goes low to his right to take a catch from his first delivery behind the stumps in an ODI. Perfect start for Australia
a bit straighter this time, Fletcher pushes to midwicket and gets off the mark
outside off and moving away a fraction, Gayle leaves
probing outside off again, Gayle shapes to play and then gets the bat out of the way
more work for Ronchi behind the stumps as Gayle leaves outside off
left alone again, a hint of shape in to Gayle this time
on line straight away, Fletcher defends
outside off and Fletcher cuts very hard, but straight to backward point where Ponting does the fielding
this one bounces a touch more, Fletcher drops the bottom hand off the handle and the ball lobs up off his gloves, drops a couple of metres in front of him
defended on the front foot now
a hint of inswing, Fletcher works it straight down into the turf
tries to work one off his pads behind square, there's some debate amongst the batsmen whether to run but in the end they make it through
outside off stump, Fletcher thinks about playing and then leaves
this time he does play, some seam away though from Lee and it beats the edge of Fletcher's bat
oh, and beats the bat again, this one was even closer to the bat. He's moving it away just a fraction and Fletcher is drawn into the shot
good pace and bounce, this time Fletcher leaves
fuller ball this time, just outside off and Fletcher plays it really well, getting the full face of the bat on a well-timed off drive that races away between cover and mid off
probing outside off again, left alone
outside off stump and Gayle defends
watchfully defended again
down leg side, Gayle tries to glance and can't connect, that's certainly a wide
Gayle solid in defence as Bracken goes back to the off stump line
pushed away towards point
straighter ball now, Gayle carefully nudges to leg
left alone outside off
turned away to leg
left alone outside off, some outswing there for Lee
pushed away to midwicket
that is fast and short, but it's just a fraction too short and well over Fletcher's head, so it's a wide
oh, that's a very good ball, on a good length and moving away off the seam, Fletcher tries to drive and it beats is bat by what must have been millimetres
this time Fletcher tries to cut hard, and again it beats the bat
driven uppishly this time, it falls a couple of metres short of mid off
Gayle defends to cover, he's being understandably cautious
nudged away defensively to cover again, he's still not off the mark
a little wider this time, Gayle gets on the board with a late cut that runs away to third man

oh dear, Fletcher almost gets himself run out in casual fashion like in the first ODI. He tucked it behind square and took off immediately, Gayle said no, and Fletcher slowly turned and strolled back, really not aware that a throw was coming in from square leg
pushed away defensively
extra bounce from Bracken, it surprises Fletcher, who gets the bottom hand off the bat and defends
angled across Gayle, who leaves
testing Gayle with a slightly fuller ball right on line, Gayle gets the bat down and defends
another cracking ball from Lee. It's pitched on leg, seamed away from Gayle, who was really squared up and it beats the outside edge
another one tests Gayle, it straightens a touch and there's some brave judgement from Gayle to leave that one
and Gayle finally gets one he can go after. A little wide outside off, Gayle drives off the back foot through cover and it flies away in the air for four
fullish ball, Gayle drives to mid off and the next one will be a free hit as Lee has overstepped

and Fletcher makes good use of the free hit. Lee digs one in short outside off, Fletcher chases it with a not-very-pretty but highly effective slap that flies in the air between mid off and cover and away to the boundary
good pace immediately from Johnson, Gayle pushes it away to point
big shouts from Johnson and the Australians, Gayle wafts outside off and there may have been some sort of noise as it went through to Ronchi but Asad Rauf is not interested
left alone outside off now
what a powerful shot! Gayle picks up a half-volley from outside off and just slaps it over mid on, that's one bounce and over the boundary

Gayle goes on the attack again and it brings his downfall. Johnson went a touch shorter, it's onto Gayle quicker than he expected and his attempted pull lobs up to mid off where it's a regulation catch for Ponting
fast ball outside off, Chanderpaul leaves
on the stumps now, Fletcher pushes away to square leg
slower ball this time, it's straight again and Fletcher defends
outside off, no real movement now and it's prodded back down the pitch
punched away defensively to cover
driven away to cover again, Fletcher playing Lee a bit better now
fast and outside off, Fletcher flashes the bat and it beats his outside edge, he may have half pulled out of the shot at the last minute as well
left alone outside off
tighter line now, Chanderpaul defends
extra bounce from Johnson, but it's wide enough that Chanderpaul can leave comfortably
Johnson drags this one too wide of off again, Chanderpaul leaves
strays down leg side this time, that's certainly a wide
on the stumps and defended
left alone outside off

on the pads first up, Fletcher flicks it deliberately in the air and safely over midwicket, not timed well enough to get to the boundary and Chanderpaul, perhaps hampered by his calf problem, doesn't want a third
punched away to cover
too short from Watson, Fletcher quickly gets on the back foot and swivels a pull forward of square leg for a well-placed boundary
slower delivery from Watson, it's outside off so Fletcher just lets it go
this one tests Fletcher a bit more, it's perhaps a shade quicker and nipping in a touch, Fletcher manages to defend but it nearly got through him
this one whizzes past the edge as Fletcher tries to pull one that probably wasn't short enough
Chanderpaul angles the bat and defends to point
on the pads now and Chanderpaul clips it through midwicket to get off the mark
prodded away defensively to point
wide outside off, Chanderpaul looks to pull and can't connect
a little bit of inswing perhaps, or maybe just the angle from over the wicket, Chanderpaul leaves one that comes in and misses off stump by a few inches
solid in defence this time
outside off, no real movement and Fletcher defends
good line again, Fletcher tries to walk down the pitch a bit then checks and defends
Fletcher punches a drive wide of mid off, the fielder gets across to make a save but there's an easy single there
and Watson beats the bat, it's really just angled across him and Chanderpaul tries to push it to cover and can't make contact
left alone this time
Chanderpaul tries to cut, it doesn't bounce that much and his under-edge goes into the ground and through to Ronchi
and thats a wide well down leg as Johnson struggles for rhythm
much better delivery, right up there on the stumps, but he's overstepped, so we have another free hit ... what can Fletcher do with it this time?
its pretty full and he makes room, carving to a diving Ponting at mid-off
good line, plugging away outside off and Chanders leaves it be
overpitched on off stump and he lazily flicks to midwicket
change of pace, pitches in line and straightens, tapped to midwicket
there in the slot and he drives it through the gap between cover and mid-off, flowing shot on the up, pushing with an open faced
short and wide, asking for trouble, but the energetic and athletic Michael Clarke cuts off a hard slap at backward point
good stuff, bringing Fletcher onto the front foot, defending
straighter one, he gets across and mistimes the nudge, but into the gap
good length outside off, he opens the face and steers to point
stands back and drives a length ball back to Watson's right
eases forward and pushes a fuller one to backward point
back and across and defends a shorter one with an inside-edge
gets it on a pretty good length and Fletcher defends to point

silly shot sends Fletcher packing, as he looks to pull one not short enough for the shot and the error in judgment costs him plenty, the ball sneaking back under his bat to rearrange the furniture, and doesn't Hopes love it?
short of a length and he gets back and across to defend
nips in off a short length and he plays it across to midwicket
fuller in length and he again gets back and across to defend
now Bravo gets well forward and runs the ball to backward point
short of a length, Chanders gets back and punches right to cover
touch too short and he pulls from outside off stump, making sure to keep the ball low, and harries a couple as deep midwicket runs around
short again, this time a firm back-foot shot is intercepted at point
fuller ball, he uses his feet and drives to cover, sending Bravo back
cramped for room, he chops the ball down to backward point
shapes to get back and across and work the ball into the gap at midwicket, but the short ball length has him playing awkwardly to backward point again
well punched off the back foot, but he can't pierce backward point
straighter line and Bravo gets into position, defending back to Hopes
gets across and tries to flick this one away, but he misses out and gets rapped above the flap as the ball angles down
repeating the shot, he's late on it and pushes to short midwicket
tight bowling from Hopes, nipping it back and Bravo taps it down
opens his account by gently steering a wide one down to third man
shuffles across and turns the ball past midwicket, there's some poor calling and responding, Bravo wanting the run and Chanderpaul hesitating
again he tries to whip the ball across the line but this one's short and angling and and strikes him above the knee roll and below the midriff, above the stumps
crafty change of pace, gets Bravo onto the front foot and defending
drives a near yorker-length ball with a flourish to the man at mid-on
there's the yorker, on off stump, and Bravo digs it out in time
Watson changes the length and Bravo defends off the back foot
gets across and plays with soft hands, dabbing through gully
bouncer now, surprising Bravo as he shapes to come forward and across, but has to rear his head back out of the ball's way
good-length ball outside off, Bravo hops across and defends to point
slides down leg stump, Bravo misses, Ronchi dives to collect
a bit too straight and it allows him to clip past midwicket
full length just outside off stump and Chanders defends it back
this one forces him onto the back foot and he eases it to point
well played, tucking the ball with the angle down to fine leg
short and he cuts well but on the bounce to Clarke at point
full and he swings agriculturally across the line to midwicket
overpitched, fractionally, and he squeezes it past cover and point

would you look at that? Bravo, trying to work the ball across the line all innings, ends up clipping a slower ball from Watson out to deep midwicket where Hussey, focusing superbly on the ball against the sun, takes the easiest of catches, didn't have to move an inch
short of a length and he gets back into line and defends
leans forward and square-drives a loopy delivery to point
too straight and Chanders picks it off for a single to square leg
good ball, pinning him back in his crease, defending
beaten on the forward defensive, that ball straightening well
onto the front foot again, this time pushing towards the off
back of a length and Browne defends it patiently as pressure builds
low looping full toss, clipped across to midwicket for one
quicker, flatter, sliding down leg and he gets an inside-edge
drifts in again and Browne defends poorly, bat coming down late
good delivery, this one spinning away and clipping something before nestling in Ronchi's gloves, they all ask the question but the umpire is unmoved ... I need to see a replay of that
defended back to Clarke, nervously
full and flat, worked into the gap for one
back and across, shapes to work it across but it late on the shot
tucked up again, he gets bat on it but mistimes it completely
back and across this time, pushing the short one to point
straighter one, middle and off, he gets back and defends
no footwork at all, just pushing from the crease, inside-edge that time
first positive shot he's played, driving the fuller ball to mid-off
low and flat on about off stump, turned away to midwicket
some more air now and he on-drives past the nonstriker
some turn and loop, pitching wide of off and spinning away

well held by White at slip, on the second attempt! Clarke works his magic again, getting this ball to spin away from Browne, who gets back and pushes and the edge is snapped up, White first fumbling and then taking it diving behind Ronchi
comes out first ball and tries to defend, misses by some ways and ball clips pad but the appeal is turned down because he was way forward
what in the world is he thinking? Second ball into his innings, Pollard plays a stupid shot, just chipping the ball over mid-off and straight into the fielder's waiting palms near long-off
fullish and moving away outside, and he leaves that one alone
misses a cut, cramped for room and feet not moving, as the ball jags back in .. I'm at a loss for words as to why the West Indians are flashing shots two balls into their time at the crease
leaves this one, which comes back in from wide of the crease
short of a length and now Sammy gets in line to defend it back
comes forward, thinking about playing, but sees the length and leaves
Hopes works that same channel and Sammy opts to leave again
full and flat on off stump, driven back to Clarke's left side
some loop now, it dips, lands and Chanders edges past Ronchi
back to flat on middle and leg and he drives to long-on
fired in down the legs, Sammy makes room and drives to mid-off
full and flat outside off stump, Chanders flicks to midwicket
drifts into his him and he's squared up, getting a leading-edge to point
runs first up with an easy dab down past gully to third man
change of pace, fullish outside off stump, Sammy makes room and is nearly beaten by the slowness but ends up chopping the ball towards point

shouts of catch it as Chanderpaul clips the slower ball in the air down towards long-on, where Hopes runs around and ends up copping the ball where it hurts, after it drops just in front of him, he makes sure to return it before attending to his injured area ... thats going to knock the wind out of him
back of a length outside off stump and he leaves this one be
tries to cut a short one but mistimes the shot to Clarke at point
slower, wider, fuller, and he prods it into the covers for one
flat on middle and off and he turns it to Ponting at midwicket
thinks about hammering it away but defends back to Clarke
fractionally short and he thinks now about cutting, but resists
full and flat and he mistimes a booming drive to cover
ends up all cramped for room, shuffling around, inside-edges to leg
short and he gets on top, cutting backward of point to keep strike
fullish on about off stump, casually clipped to midwicket
holds back the length, slants it across, and Sammy is beaten
again he shapes to heave it but cannot judge the length and in the end has to play some weird sort of back-foot defensive to point
fuller length on the stumps, Sammy opens the face and nudges to cover
gets well across and cannot get bat on ball, sliding down leg, but runs a leg bye as the fielder is deep at square leg
now he connects on what he's been aiming at for a while, backing away and scooping over the infield and the ball drops short of deep mid-off
full and flat and he drives inside-out to the man at cover
bit shorter, he gets back and cuts to point
comes forward and drives this one back and Clarke fields
now thats hit out of the screws, simply thumped back over Clarke's head as he lands that ball on a length, where Sammy wants it
swings again and inside-edges towards cover that time
the end is nigh, with Sammy slogging that one tossed up on a length right down Johnson's throat at long-on
walks into this shot, timing a drive well past cover to open his account
comes forward and is beaten for pace, driving back to Bracken
slower ball on a short length, this time Chanders picks it and opens the face of the bat to steer with the width down to third man
comes down, Bracken bowls a full toss and its patted back
clears his front leg and drills a length ball uppishly to long-off
full on about off stump and he lazily clips it past midwicket
drops it short and he pulls past square leg out to a diving sweeper, looks likes Hopes out there, well stopped
this one's full and flat on middle and leg and he sweeps
that lands on a length and Powell drives pleasingly towards cover
wrong line and thats driven towards midwicket this time
top shot, just clearing the front foot and teeing off very hard for a straight six, and that needs to be recovered from between the seats down there
quicker, flatter, shorter and he limply defends from his crease
drivable length and Chanderpaul does so, out past extra cover
lands on a length and Powell, making room, clubs it back past Hopes and Chanderpaul for a single towards mid-on
reaches across and swings this over midwicket, on the bounce
oh he's hit that off the middle, has Powell, just walking down and knocking that rows back over midwicket for half a dozen
low full toss this time, Powell steps aside and drives past cover
full and wide, he reaches out and steers past backward point for a single that raises the West Indies' 100 in 34 overs
loosener to start off with, slow and loopy outside leg stump, and Chanders turns that into the gap at square leg and midwicket
dances down, making room, but can't hit the slower ball
thats another good shot, Powell walking across his stumps to make sure he's inside the line of the slower ball before paddle-pulling past Lee at short fine leg
timber! Watson takes out Powell's off stump with a yorker-length delivery, the tail-ender exposing his sticks and playing all over the ball
runs first up, as Benn slashes the slower ball just over gully
dances down and heaves, agriculturally inside-edging down to fine leg where a dive saves runs
another decent shot, Benn turning this one past square leg for two
makes room, skips down, closes his eyes, swings, and misses
how did that miss? Benn swings across the line, the ball is fuller and narrowly misses leg stump after brushing his pads, and then the big man nearly collapses
massive slog again, missing by miles, Chanders strolls down for a chat
he's not listening to a word his senior team-mate has to say! Benn! He's just going for broke, swinging wildly and missing, again he gets a word from Chanderpaul .. is it worth it?
finally connects, driving a fuller ball down to mid-off for one
swings across the line, scooping in the air and it drops safely
sweeps from outside off stump, placing it into the gap at square leg and Marsh slides on the ropes after covering plenty of ground, and fires in a throw
slower ball swings in, he chips across the line, missing
doesn't get the yorker right and thats driven in the air to long-on
slaps that cross-batted from outside off past midwicket
again Benn skips down and toe-ends the wide ball towards cover
lands it on a length, Benn swings and misses once again
swings again, this time getting bat and dripping to to square leg
short of a length on off stump, Chanders defends and sets off
skips down the track, exposing the sticks, Lee follows him with a half-tracker and Benn, taking his eyes off the ball, swats and connects with air
much fuller, almost a yorker, somehow thats inside-edged to fine leg
fast and very full outside leg, Benn backs away and again gets a thick inside-edge down to the man at fine leg, so Lee stays on 299 wickets for now
there's a boundary, as Benn swats a full toss between midwicket and mid-on, Ponting dives on the ropes and can't stop the four, kicking the ground in disgust
slower ball, again he swings it away and this time there's protection
swings across the line, slogging towards midwicket for one
skips down, swings, top-edges a slower ball miles up in the air but it drops smack between long-on and long-off converging down there
full and wide, Chanders slices the ball towards point for one
and again ... you know the drill ... slower ball, full and not that wide, big back-swing, eyes shut, mentally imagining deep midwicket, massive heave, and a miss
single now, tucked away from middle and leg to fine leg
backs away, slogs this one down to mid-on, again it drops safely
he too slogs and scoops into the gap at square leg for one
makes room and drives hard, but cant beat the men at cover
slices this one off the back foot just over backward point
full on the stumps and he flicks this out to deep midwicket
short of a length, he gets back and runs it to backward point
slower and fuller, driven back to Bracken, who sticks out his left hand and ricochets onto the stumps, then Chanderpaul calls for the single
fullish outside off, he tries to tip and run but Bracken fields it
slow, full, wide, Benn reaches out and drives to cover
digs in the short one and Benn loses sight, swerving away
finishes the match with a slogged single out to deep midwicket
